commit.message:
v2.601

        - allow using an Authen::SASL instance via sasl_authenticator as an
          alternative to username asd password (thanks, Erik Huelsmann!)

remove an obsoleted mock test

Previously, you could create an SMTP transport with a username but no
password.  This was basically pointless, since it would always fail.
It now dies during object construction, so this code wouldn't return a
Failure from trying to send, it would just throw.

I've deleted the test.
prep Changes for next release

Merge pull request #77 from ehuelsmann/issue-71

Close #71: Allow explicit specification of SASL mechanisms

commit.message: tweak some code layout before merge
Incorporate further review comments about coding style
Incorporate review comment from @rjbs

Add `sasl_authenticator` attribute

Having the option to pass an Authen::SASL instance adds flexibility.

Closes #71.

Move password availability check to construction time

The attribute is read-only, so it's functionally equivalent to check
at creation time.
